        "rich_text_ccxpK9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>There is something magical about the moment when you try to capture your ring on your camera. You hold up your hand, adjust the angle, search for the right light, and hope the photo reflects what your eyes see. But for many people, the result is confusing. The diamond looks flat, the sparkle disappears, and even the prettiest ring loses its charm in the picture. </p><p>If you have ever taken <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-ring\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"engagement ring \">engagement ring </a>photos and wondered why the glow is missing, you are not alone. Even the most beautiful ring can look dull on camera if a few small details while taking the photo are off. From stiff poses to low light to filters that blur the shine, these simple mistakes can affect everything from your engagement ring poses to your close up ring pic moments.</p><p>The good news is that you can fix all of it with ease. You do not need professional equipment or photography skills. With a few simple adjustments, your engagement ring pics can look clear, bright, and full of life. </p><p>Let us look at some common mistakes and the easy ways to avoid them, so every photo does justice to your ring and the story it carries.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
